{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17625268","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17625268"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T16:22:45+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T16:22:45+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17012"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17012","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17012"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.11,0,0.7,0.11,0.07]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9702"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"68248"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9702","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9702"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17012"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53704"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4939"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"5357"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22837"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22843"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"68248","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/68248"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA public health researcher is studying disparities in healthcare outcomes between different racial and ethnic groups in Australia. The investigation reveals systematic differences in access to healthcare services, treatment patterns, and health outcomes that persist even when controlling for socioeconomic status.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes institutional racism in healthcare?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Unconscious biases affecting clinical decision-making","Inadequate cultural competency training for healthcare staff","Organisational policies and practices that systematically disadvantage certain racial groups","Unequal distribution of healthcare facilities in diverse communities","Limited representation of minority groups in healthcare leadership"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOrganisational policies and practices that systematically disadvantage certain racial groups\u003C/strong\u003E accurately describes institutional racism in healthcare. This form of racism exists within the structures, policies, and practices of healthcare institutions, regardless of individual intent.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EUnconscious biases affecting clinical decision-making\u003C/strong\u003E describes individual-level cognitive biases rather than systemic institutional issues.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInadequate cultural competency training\u003C/strong\u003E is one contributor to healthcare disparities but does not capture the broader structural nature of institutional racism.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EUnequal distribution of healthcare facilities\u003C/strong\u003E is one manifestation of institutional racism rather than its fundamental definition.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELimited representation of minority groups in healthcare leadership\u003C/strong\u003E is an outcome of institutional racism rather than its definition.\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EInstitutional racism in healthcare manifests through policies, procedures, and organisational cultures that create and maintain racial disparities in health outcomes. These systemic issues persist independently of individual attitudes or intentions.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Institutional racism refers to policies, practices, and cultural norms within organisations that disadvantage certain racial or ethnic groups.","Institutional racism can exist without individual prejudice through embedded systems and structures.","Healthcare outcomes are negatively impacted by institutional racism through reduced access, different treatment patterns, and communication barriers."],"references":["Shultz JM, Sullivan LM, Galea S. Public Health: An Introduction to the Science and Practice of Population Health. Springer Publishing Company; 2021."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53704"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17012"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53704","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/53704"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-09T15:31:03+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-09T15:32:18+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9702"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"68248"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Reme